lenders.occupational_info:
Required running capital and buyout R 150,000-00


Hi There
My name is Abduragiem (Kim) Stofberg (PDP) I have recently entered into partnership with somebody, however my partner has lost interest in the company mainly because he does not understand the cut to size operation and the fact that he comes from a machining back ground spends little time in the company that we have established.
My dilemma is this, I would like to take over this company, simply because I have gain so much ground with the customer and supplier alike, When I take over this company I would be requiring financial assistance for stock and to expand, meaning more machinery which means more staff.
I have already approached several institutions with my business plan but they either take to long with the process or don’t even bother coming back to me at all or they state that the company is only 6 months old.
I do understand that the business is only six months old but this company carries great potential and this can be shown by means of the previous month’s figures.
About the company, it is a cut to size of steel company which the process gets done by means of a profiling machine, we have a small client base and looking for more every day, we have the technical expertise and have the knowledge of processing the work to customer’s specifications. I myself am a draft-man by trade and have 23years experience in the engineering field and am trying to spear head or to assist people of color in breaking into this industry which was once or still is by dominated by people of non-color.
Your urgent assistance in this scenario will be highly appreciative
Regards and thank you
